entries.femaleVariant: Mosley must be talented to stop you in the GIM.
Why do you want to make contact with Alt?
Mosley must have some nifty nerves to get the better of you. What happened at the GIM,  exactly?
When we sent Ti Neptune for recon, we did not know what we were up against.
If I had not followed him, they would have cracked his ICE like a lobster shell and used his interface to breach our BBS.
Lucky for them, you tried to help. Two for the price of one.
I knew Placide would find a way.
Why contact Alt? Her specifically, I mean.
Evelyn beat you to it in Konpeki.
Honestly, gotta be pretty embarrassing a doll beat you at your own game.
Sure there are plent of other wild AIs that didn't require swipin' Arasaka tech first.
entries.maleVariant: I'm sure there are plent of other wild AIs that didn't require swipin' Arasaka tech first.

entries.femaleVariant: But of them all, only Alt was once human.
Counting on mutual understanding, huh?
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Mwen te espere manzè pa tap gaye twòp nan men yo." t="I hoped she would not be completely unstable." b="" a=""/>
Evelyn copied the data – without your knowledge  – then assembled her own team and reached Yorinobu before you.
Indeed. Impressive from what I heard.
People are saying she left an impression.
Didn't look for the biochip after?
Let's talk about something else.
On to other things…
Left quite a few people 'round town stunned.
entries.maleVariant: Oh, she left quite a few people 'round town stunned.

entries.femaleVariant: Didn't bother lookin' for the chip after the heist?
Because, for the city, it was the night old man Arasaka died.
<mothertongue l="creo" m="enbesils" b="None know that several " a=" were zero'd in de process, and one unlucky mercenary put a time bomb in their brain."/>
We did.
Didn't work out, I see.
Nothing appeared Net-wide about de Relic.
You kept quiet. You did well to do so.
